,Recommended,251470,16414582,"Posted: 15 June, 2015",all,kinggimped,"Verdict:If you have a few Xbox360 controllers and some meatspace friends who can come over and play this game with you,you should buy it now.If you don't have controllers or real life friends to play with,you definitely shouldn't buy it.Or you should buy controllers, make some friends, and then buy the game.---It's a great local multiplayer game. One of those 'easy to learn, hard to master' type deals. The mechanics are solid, it controls well, and once everybody is familiar with it you can have some incredibly intense and fun games with your buddies. Luck plays a big part early on, but once you get the hang of it, your deaths are very rarely anybody else's fault but your own.At its best the game is satisfyingly choreographic - players leap and grapple from ledge to ledge, shots collide mid-air, arrows can be dodged (and caught mid-air) with the right timing, corpses are pinned to walls, and the instant replay at the end of each round allows you to enjoy the sheer frenzy of what just happened at your leisure.Look up some multiplayer gameplay videos for the game on YouTube, those are going to be the best gauge of whether or not you're going to enjoy what's on offer here.Ignore the reviews complaining that the single player isn't strong. This is a multiplayer game. If you bought it for the single player, it's your own fault that you're not enjoying it. It's a bonus there's even a solo mode included in the game."
