,Recommended,251470,16450376,"Posted: 16 June, 2015",all,Micah,"An incredibly fun, addictive, competitive, well-balanced, and surprisingly deep game. My family is playing it constantly, every day. I also find it quite fun to play through co-op levels as a solo player.One word of warning: the game is a bit pricey just by itself, but to really get the most out of it you'll very likely want the expansion. The expansion's features are fully integrated into the core game, but if  you try to use them it'll tell you you have to buy the DLC. :-pWithout the expansion, you can only play co-op with 2 players, each of whom has a fixed number of lives. The expansion adds co-op levels for up to 4 players, but there's no lives store - if a player dies, another player has to revive him, and if all players are dead the game's over (continuing is possible). These worlds can also be played solo mode with fixed lives, and unlike the core game worlds you can continue if you die on a particular level.The versus mode is quite fun, and does a great job of balancing skill levels without dampening the fun (if you're winning, you get fewer arrows, and if you're way behind you start with a shield). The number of interesting outcomes for a battle seems quite high, and I find myself saving replay GIFs regularly. Neat little details abound, such as the way you can knock someone's hood or hat off if your arrow merely brushes through their hair instead of hitting them squarely. Occasionally some odd tweak will appear unexpectedly in a co-op level, and some of these lead to unlockable new characters you can play as."
