,Recommended,251470,17020041,"Posted: 12 July, 2015",all,Damonkashu,in my top 10
,Recommended,251470,16321438,"Posted: 11 June, 2015",all,Sensual Lettuce,"Towerfall is one of the local multiplayer indie games that I've ever played. I have seen veteran gamers and people who don't play games both get hooked on Towerfall after playing just a few rounds. It is that accessible and easy to get into. But that's not to say that it's easy - it'll take countless hours of gameplay to understand the subtle tactics which will allow you to compete at high levels of play.The art style and presentation of the game is beautiful and nostalgic to anyone who grew up with games from the SNES era in the 1990's. There is no online multiplayer but the developer has explained why many times: the game is too fast to facilitate satisfying and fair online gameplay. With that said, you will want to be playing this with friends locally because that's the way that it's meant to be played.Recent updates to Towerfall have brought so much value to the game. I recommend getting the Dark World expansion pack, even more so now that it adds Steam Workshop support. Not only is there a whole new world of user-generated Towerfall content to enjoy, but the way that all of this new content is integrated into the game is brilliant.If I could only have one local multiplayer game on Steam, I would probably choose Towerfall. Get some friends together and play Towerfall."
