76561198028637086,Recommended,251470,15808432,"Posted: 12 May, 2015",all,CP Lana,"Alright. so quick heads up, This game does NOT have network play. if you're looking to play online, then this is NOT the game for you. period.There is no feasable way to add network play to a game like this, and still have it be playable. it is just far too twitchy for that.so with that out of the way...Towerfall is an incredibly twitchy 2D arena game. fast reflexes are what will win you the day here, and I absolutely love that.A variety of powerups and maps really spice up the gameplay, so it will rarely ever feel stale. if you have a couple of friends you can get together, and a few xbox controllers lying around, give this a shot.Now for the 'co-op'this is the bit that I play the most, as the only other major gamer in my group of friends HATES twitch games like this. (likely because he has the lightning-fast reflexes of a dead sloth, and the hand-eye coordination of a blind snake, but hey.) I personally found the 'co-op' enjoyable. frustrating at times, but enjoyable. I've experienced cheap deaths a-plenty, but nothing feels more satesfactory as clearing those tough-as-nails stages on Hardcore mode.If I had to point out one issue I have with it, that would be that co-op's idea of challenge is to swarm you with enemies, up until you fight against the major boss (which I would have liked to see more of. Dark World delivers that.)but seeing as how this is a game about reflexes, that's somewhat understandable."
