,Recommended,251470,9559702,"Posted: 19 March, 2014",all,ZacFierce,"This is, thus far, the most enjoyable multiplayer game I've ever played. A party game in the truest sense, with controls easy enough to pick up that anyone can start playing in seconds. The depth of combat mechanics paired with tight controls leads to rewarding gameplay for hardcore players who can think fast and move even faster. The art style is impeccable, down to the smallest detail in animation. The music is catchy. The gameplay, sublime.That said, do not buy this game.Once more:DO NOT BUY THIS GAME.**Unless you know what you're getting into. TowerFall was designed as a local co-op experience.There is no online multiplayer, and there might never be.That means if you want to play with friends, and get the most out of this game, you're gonna have to have some controllers handy. Heck, if you want to play it well, you're gonna need a controller yourself! There is singleplayer content, and it is pretty fun, but the meat of TowerFall is playing with friends, and you're gonna need controllers if you want to do that locally on a PC.If you have at least one controller at your disposal, you're doing yourself a disservice by not owning this game. If you don't, hold off unless you acquire a controller (or 4) in the future. This game is incredible, and deserves your attention, but keep in mind that you won't be able to enjoy it without the proper gear."
