76561197961494531,Recommended,251470,9435385,"Posted: 11 March, 2014",all,Rapscallion,"TowerFall Ascension is not for the faint-hearted. It may appear very simple, but it can become extremely challenging very quickly. Here's a video giving you my thoughts on the single-player side of the game (for those of us who have a hard time getting friends over).http://youtu.be/K81IX5qE5JQIn summary, here are the pros and cons of the game (some as ? because it varies on the person)+ Simple controls. It makes it easy for anyone to pick up and play.+ High skill ceiling. While moving, shooting, jumping, and dodging are the only controls, using them all in combination to navigate the diverse courses while shooting down foes is more than challenging to say the least.+ Fluid gameplay. Everything responds exactly how you expect it to and when you expect it to.+ Local Multiplayer is a blast. It's very competitive, and when you win, damn do you feel good.+ Highly satisfying when you perform well. It takes a lot of skill to do this, and when you do, you know it.+ A lot of enemy variety with different mechanics.? Extremely challenging. You can make it so difficult, that you will never beat a level unless you perform near perfection. The one-hit-kill system makes this so.? Even on normal, it doesn't hold your hand. You will die and fail multiple times before you learn the map's patterns and enemies so you can complete it. The time will differ greatly from person to person.? The single player is decent. It's nowhere near as fun as the multiplayer, but that's to be expected of most games.- No tutorial. The best I could find was something in the options menu that gives you hints, but you have to look for it. With something as difficult as this, anything that helps is greatly appreciated.- IMO, I wish they used better quality sprites like the ones they have when you select your character. Just a small ding for this, though. Graphics only matter to a certain extent.- This can be very frustrating in later levels. You just can't see everything that's coming at you, and when enemies fill the screen, it only makes it that much worse. Best thing to do is set it down and come back later, but that may be never depending on how bad it♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥you off.- It's local multiplayer only. It cuts off a really good part of the game for those people who can't get people over to play. And I can't help but feel this game would've really benifited from having online servers so you can play multiplayer anytime.In conclusion, get it for the multiplayer. You're gonna have a blast with it. If you have time to kill and like a challenge, then consider getting it for the single player. It's not bad for the price.*Update*If you guys wanna see what the Co-op Quest is like, here's another video highlighting the mayhem and hilarity that it brings. To be honest, I think it even makes this game more challenging than doing it alone.http://youtu.be/Pzcb2Lb2Jbw*Final Update*Here is some of the Versus mode. There is more on our channel if you wish to see it.http://youtu.be/ljLMgculgUI"
