,Recommended,251470,27958528,"Posted: 28 November, 2016",all,Adinimys,"I never took the time to write a review before because I wanted to do it correctly and elaborate my opinion.But with the steam awards badge I needed to jump in and write a review to get the full badge. I didn't what to rush a review to get this badge so I choose the game I nominated for which the review is the simplest : the game I nominated in the custom category as ""local multiplayer essential"".My opinion on it is easy to express : it's simply awsome ! :DWhenever we are aving LANs with friends or are just a small group gathered there is often a time when we want to have fun with a local multiplayer game and Towerfall is the go-to game in this case.It's really simple to learn but offers a lot of surprising and intense enconters thanks to the variety of arrows, the little interaction with terrain, the warping of the map in a snake-like fation, the dodges...And all of this awsome gameplay is coming with beatifull pixel art graphics and a variety of little fun touches that you enjoy discovering throughout the game : the characters and map unlocks, the hats that can be removed by an arrow coming too close, the original awards at the end of each match...Add to this a coop and a challenge mode that are both solid (even if for me the core of the game is the versus) and the possibility to tweak the rules of the match to add interesting twists (controlable ghosts, exploding bodies, slow time...) and you've good an awsome game with a clean and elegant design that is always fun to play for one more match :DPlus, the extension is good too but I'll talk about it in a specific review if I do one (spoiler alert : new cool maps/arrow/character design and bosses 4-player coop => it's really good ^^)"
