,Recommended,251470,34726114,Posted: 3 September,all,KatanaKat58,"This is my favorite multiplayer game on Steam. There's nothing better than the panic of sitting on the couch with a friend and shouting at the TV while we scramble to stomp on one another's heads since we've already launched every arrow in our arsenal. This game has a wonderful cooperative quest mode for one or more players in addition to its versus mode. It can be very challenging at times but it always feels rewarding to complete a difficult stage. There's also a time attack mode for striking dummies and showing off.Everything is animated beautifully, this isn't just another ""retro"" styled game with so much clunky movement. There are so many tiny details. A lot of care was put into making this game breathe; it looks and sounds wonderful.The Dark World DLC is a good expansion on the game, it adds more cooperative levels, additional bosses to take down, alternate archer characters/outfits, as well as the addition of Steam Workshop support; you can create your own versus stages and share them with the community.IF Towerfall Ascension had online multiplayer I doubt I'd play much of anything else!"
